content:
Navigate Action

The Navigate Action element directs users to various Salesforce experiences from an OmniScript.

Drag the Navigate Action into the OmniScript's structure panel. If rendered in a Step, it becomes a clickable button. If between steps, it fires automatically.

(Optional) Select a Button Variant and Icon name for rendering as a button.

Replace the existing entry in browser history by setting Replace to Yes. This redirects users to a new tab.

After completion, Steps and other OmniScript elements run. However, if users navigate away from the OmniScript, Integration Procedures stop running asynchronously invoked.

(Optional) Enable LWC PubSub Message to send messages to separate Lightning web components.

Determine the Salesforce experience by selecting a PageReference type:

* App: Launches an app.
* Community Named Page: Directs users to a community page.
* Component: Navigates to Aura or Lightning components.
* Current Page: Triggers a page update on the current page.
* Knowledge Article: Displays knowledge articles.
* Login: Opens a community login page.
* Named Page: Opens a standard named page.
* Navigation Item: Displays mapped content on a custom tab.
* Object: Directs users to an object page.
* Record: Opens a page interacting with a record.
* Record Relationship: Opens pages interacting with a record relationship.
* Restart OmniScript: Returns users to the beginning of the OmniScript and clears data.
* Vlocity OmniScript: Launches a separate OmniScript.
* Web Page: Opens an external URL.

Supported pageReference types include App, Community Named Page, Component, Current Page, Knowledge Article, Login, Named Page, Navigation Item, Object, Record, Record Relationship, Restart OmniScript, Vlocity OmniScript, and Web Page.
title: OmniStudio Navigation and Actions
